WEBVTT

00:04.905 --> 00:06.407
OK, THAT GOES
IN THE BASEMENT.

00:06.440 --> 00:08.042
YOU'RE DRAGGIN' IT.
YOU'RE DRAGGIN' IT.

00:08.076 --> 00:10.611
YOU'RE LUCKY
I'M NOT THROWING IT.

00:10.644 --> 00:11.745
WELL, WEDDING'S
OVER EARLY.

00:11.779 --> 00:13.281
DID YOU BRING
ME BACK SOME CAKE?

00:13.314 --> 00:15.116
THE WEDDING
HASN'T STARTED, DAD.

00:15.149 --> 00:16.484
WELL, I THOUGHT
YOU AND EDDIE

00:16.517 --> 00:18.086
WERE PLAYING
THE RECEPTION.

00:18.119 --> 00:19.120
THAT HAD BEEN THE PLAN.

00:19.153 --> 00:20.321
YEAH, WELL,
AT THE, UH, SOUND CHECK

00:20.354 --> 00:23.057
WE HAD SOME
ARTISTIC DIFFERENCES.

00:23.091 --> 00:24.058
GIMME MY GUITAR.

00:24.092 --> 00:26.494
COME AND GET IT,
.

00:33.134 --> 00:35.669
YOU BOYS WERE NEVER
ANY GOOD AT SHARING.

00:35.703 --> 00:37.171
OH, MAN, DAD,

00:37.205 --> 00:39.039
I NEED A BEER.

00:43.111 --> 00:43.877
HI, WHERE'S SEAN?

00:43.911 --> 00:46.080
CLAUDIA, I BET
YOU BROUGHT ME CAKE.

00:46.114 --> 00:48.249
NO. NO, NO, CAKE.

00:48.282 --> 00:49.383
SEAN?
Sean: UH...

00:49.417 --> 00:50.118
HI, THERE YOU ARE.

00:50.151 --> 00:51.285
NO, CLAUDIA,
I'M NOT GOIN' BACK.

00:51.319 --> 00:52.386
OH, YES, YOU ARE.
NO, I'M NOT.

00:52.420 --> 00:54.755
YES, YOU ARE.
YOU HAVE TO PLAY.
IT'S LINA'S WEDDING.

00:54.788 --> 00:55.556
I DON'T WANT TO!
YEAH, WELL, I DON'T

00:55.589 --> 00:57.625
WANNA WEAR A DRESS
THAT MAKES MY ASS

00:57.658 --> 00:59.827
LOOK LIKE A BIRTHDAY
PRESENT...

00:59.860 --> 01:02.330
BUT I'M
A BRIDESMAID,
SO HERE I AM.

01:02.963 --> 01:04.398
NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO!

01:04.432 --> 01:05.633
LILY, TAKE THAT STUFF
BACK OUT TO THE CAR

01:05.666 --> 01:07.235
BECAUSE YOUR DAD
IS GONNA
PLAY THIS WEDDING.

01:07.268 --> 01:09.103
NO, YOU DON'T,
'CAUSE I'M NOT
GOIN' BACK,

01:09.137 --> 01:10.204
AND THIS WOULDN'T
BE A PROBLEM

01:10.238 --> 01:12.806
IF YOU HADN'T
DRAGGED ME INTO IT
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

01:12.840 --> 01:14.308
MY WEDDING'S
IN A WEEK,

01:14.342 --> 01:15.743
AND MY BAND
CANCELS ON ME?

01:15.776 --> 01:18.246
HONEY,
THESE THINGS HAPPEN.

01:18.279 --> 01:19.347
2 DAYS
BEFORE MY WEDDING,

01:19.380 --> 01:21.182
MY BABY-SITTER
CANCELED ON ME.

01:21.215 --> 01:22.783
MY CATERER'S
FREAKING OUT ON ME,

01:22.816 --> 01:25.386
I'VE GOT NO FLOWERS,
AND NOW THIS?

01:25.419 --> 01:28.122
IT'S SUPPOSED
TO BE MY DAY.

01:28.156 --> 01:29.490
I KNOW. OH.

01:29.523 --> 01:31.159
COME ON. HERE, HERE.

01:31.192 --> 01:32.360
I MEAN, YOU'LL JUST--
WE'LL FIND ANOTHER BAND.

01:32.393 --> 01:36.764
NO, I WON'T.
I'VE ALREADY
TRIED EVERYWHERE.

01:36.797 --> 01:38.899
UH...

01:38.932 --> 01:40.334
OK, I'VE GOT IT.

01:40.368 --> 01:41.369
I HAVE GOT IT.
I'VE GOT IT.

01:41.402 --> 01:42.803
SEAN AND EDDIE
CAN BE YOUR BAND.

01:42.836 --> 01:45.139
SEAN AND EDDIE
HAVE A BAND?

01:45.173 --> 01:46.307
THEY USED TO,
AND THEY WERE GREAT.

01:46.340 --> 01:48.676
THAT'S IT. SEAN AND EDDIE
ARE YOUR BAND.

01:48.709 --> 01:50.444
WHAT?

02:05.593 --> 02:07.195
YOU PUT ME IN
AN IMPOSSIBLE POSITION.

02:07.228 --> 02:08.596
WELL, YOU COULD
HAVE SAID NO.

02:08.629 --> 02:10.364
I DID SAY NO.

02:11.332 --> 02:14.335
I'M SORRY. IT'S JUST,
IT'S NOT A GOOD IDEA.

02:14.368 --> 02:16.204
IT CAN BE
JUST LIKE OLD TIMES.

02:16.237 --> 02:18.739
COME ON, DO YOU
REMEMBER OLD TIMES?

02:30.818 --> 02:32.486
MAZEL TOV.

02:32.520 --> 02:33.554
YOU SUCK.

02:33.587 --> 02:36.624
IF YOU WERE A MAN,
I'D KICK YOUR ASS.

02:36.657 --> 02:38.226
TODAY, I AM A MAN.

02:38.259 --> 02:40.428
ALL RIGHT.
DON'T FREAK OUT.
DON'T FREAK OUT.

02:40.461 --> 02:43.264
COME ON, SEAN, PLEASE?
IT'LL BE FUN...

02:43.297 --> 02:46.600
AND, UM, YOU KNOW,
YOU'D BE IN A BAND
AGAIN.

02:46.634 --> 02:49.337
OH, AND YOU LIKE THAT.

02:52.506 --> 02:55.709
WHOO-HOO!

02:58.612 --> 02:59.747
OK, LINA, WE'RE IN.

02:59.780 --> 03:00.348
YES!

03:00.381 --> 03:01.749
YOU FORCED
MY HAND, BABY.

03:01.782 --> 03:02.850
NOT MY FAULT.
Lily: OK,

03:02.883 --> 03:03.984
AM I SUPPOSED
TO TAKE THE AMP

03:04.017 --> 03:05.653
TO THE BASEMENT
OR TO THE CAR?

03:05.686 --> 03:06.654
CAR.
BASEMENT.

03:06.687 --> 03:08.756
LILY, TAKE IT
TO THE CAR.

03:08.789 --> 03:10.391
TAKE IT
TO THE BASEMENT.
OHH!

03:10.424 --> 03:11.225
I'M SERIOUS!
ME, TOO!

03:11.259 --> 03:13.727
OH, FINE!
I'M GONNA
TAKE IT MYSELF.

03:13.761 --> 03:16.264
GOOD!

03:16.297 --> 03:17.565
UNH!

03:18.432 --> 03:20.634
YOU'RE MAKING
MY SWEET LITTLE GIRL

03:20.668 --> 03:22.236
LUG THIS BIG
THING AROUND?

03:22.270 --> 03:25.473
SHE'S NOT YOUR LITTLE GIRL.
SHE'S MY ROADIE.

03:27.741 --> 03:29.677
HEY, WHAT'S
THE MATTER WITH YOU?

03:29.710 --> 03:30.644
I THOUGHT
YOU AND EDDIE

03:30.678 --> 03:31.579
ENJOYED
PLAYING TOGETHER.

03:31.612 --> 03:32.980
WE DO. I WAS PSYCHED,

03:33.013 --> 03:34.715
BUT WE NEEDED
A NEW DRUMMER.

03:34.748 --> 03:36.250
LOU USED
TO BE OUR DRUMMER,

03:36.284 --> 03:38.018
BUT SADLY, LOU...

03:38.051 --> 03:40.388
LOU COULDN'T BE THERE.

03:41.722 --> 03:43.824
IT'S A DAMN SHAME.

03:43.857 --> 03:47.661
IT WON'T BE THE SAME
WITHOUT YOU, LOU.

03:47.695 --> 03:49.630
GUYS, I'M SORRY.

03:49.663 --> 03:53.000
I JUST CAN'T
GET SATURDAY OFF.

03:55.035 --> 03:56.570
Lily: WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:56.604 --> 03:57.638
OH, IS HENRY LOST AGAIN?

03:57.671 --> 04:00.274
NO, NO. WE'RE TRYING
TO GET A DRUMMER
FOR THE BAND.

04:00.308 --> 04:02.610
YOUR--YOUR--YOUR SEARCH
IS OVER, MR. FINNERTY.

04:02.643 --> 04:03.711
I'M YOUR DUDE.

04:03.744 --> 04:04.945
YOU PLAY THE DRUMS?

04:04.978 --> 04:05.813
HELL, YEAH.

04:05.846 --> 04:07.681
HE'S IN
THE MARCHING BAND.

04:07.715 --> 04:08.882
YEAH, YEAH.
CHECK ME OUT.

04:08.916 --> 04:11.018
[IMITATES DRUMS,
CYMBALS]

04:12.420 --> 04:15.423
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
I'M SURE YOU'RE GOOD.

04:15.456 --> 04:16.189
YEAH. WE GOTTA
CHECK OUT

04:16.223 --> 04:18.058
ALL THE OTHER
CANDIDATES, THOUGH.

04:21.061 --> 04:23.997
YAAAA-YEAH!

04:24.031 --> 04:27.568
[DRUMS PLAY,
CYMBALS CRASH]

04:30.371 --> 04:33.407
[PLAYS DRUMS
MARCHING STYLE]

04:42.783 --> 04:45.653
COOL EFFECT.

04:45.686 --> 04:48.522
WHAT EFFECT?

05:02.503 --> 05:03.904
HEY, MAN, THIS GIG
DOESN'T PAY A LOT.

05:03.937 --> 05:05.939
LOOK, I'M NOT ABOUT
THE MONEY, ALL RIGHT?

05:05.973 --> 05:07.675
I'M ABOUT THE MUSIC.

05:07.708 --> 05:09.577
ME, TOO.
RIGHT ON.

05:09.610 --> 05:12.646
I'LL TAKE HIS MONEY.

05:13.447 --> 05:17.418
I DIDN'T RAISE THAT BOY
TO BE A SUCKER.

05:17.918 --> 05:20.588
HOW COULD YOU LET
ME CARRY THAT AMP
ALL THE WAY TO THE CAR?

05:20.621 --> 05:22.790
I DIDN'T
WANT IT IN THE CAR.

05:25.025 --> 05:26.694
HELLO.

05:26.727 --> 05:27.528
OH, HI, LINA.

05:27.561 --> 05:31.131
YES, OF--OF COURSE
SEAN'S COMING BACK.

05:31.164 --> 05:35.603
THERE'S NOTHING--
GET A DEEJAY!

05:36.036 --> 05:37.771
SHH HEARD YOU, DUMB ASS.

05:37.805 --> 05:41.609
I'M TELLING YOU,
THERE'S NO
BABY PICTURES OF ME.

05:41.642 --> 05:42.309
SO?

05:42.342 --> 05:44.678
DO YOU REALIZE
WHAT THAT MEANS?

05:44.712 --> 05:49.417
YEAH, AFTER 2 KIDS,
MOM AND DAD GOT BORED.

05:50.584 --> 05:51.519
NO, I'M ADOPTED.

05:51.552 --> 05:56.790
W-WAIT. WHY WOULD
MOM AND DAD ADOPT YOU?

05:57.925 --> 05:59.827
WELL, BECAUSE
THEY WANTED A BOY.

05:59.860 --> 06:00.561
THEY HAD A BOY.

06:00.594 --> 06:02.896
I MEAN, ONE
WHO'S NOT SO NERDY.

06:04.565 --> 06:05.966
OK, YOU WANNA
KNOW THE TRUTH?

06:05.999 --> 06:07.701
HERE'S THE TRUTH.

06:07.735 --> 06:09.403
YOU'RE A ROBOT.

06:09.437 --> 06:11.772
A ROBOT?!
SHH!

06:11.805 --> 06:13.474
YOU'RE VERY
SOPHISTICATED.

06:13.507 --> 06:16.577
YOU COST
$14 MILLION.

06:16.610 --> 06:17.811
NO WAY.

06:17.845 --> 06:19.847
YEAH. WHY DO YOU THINK
MOM GETS SO WORRIED

06:19.880 --> 06:22.149
WHEN YOU FALL
OFF YOUR BIKE?

06:27.955 --> 06:29.022
HEY, HEY, LILY,

06:29.056 --> 06:31.158
GO GET THE AMP
OUT OF MY CAR.

06:31.191 --> 06:34.127
OOH!

06:34.728 --> 06:36.430
YOU KNOW,
SHE'S NOT VERY HAPPY

06:36.464 --> 06:37.865
ABOUT THE BAND
BREAKIN' UP.

06:37.898 --> 06:39.900
DRUMMER
DIDN'T WORK OUT.

06:39.933 --> 06:41.469
WELL, YOU KNOW
WHAT'S WEIRD?

06:41.502 --> 06:43.437
AT FIRST, THIS KID
SEEMED GREAT.

06:43.471 --> 06:45.839
YOU GUYS THINK THERE'S
GONNA BE ANY RECORD EXECS

06:45.873 --> 06:47.107
AT THIS WEDDING, OR WHAT?

06:47.140 --> 06:48.241
YOU NEVER KNOW.

06:48.275 --> 06:50.544
YOU KNOW WHO HAD
THE GREATEST WEDDING
BAND OF ALL TIME?

06:50.578 --> 06:53.447
PINK FLOYD.
THAT'S HOW THEY
STARTED OUT.

06:53.481 --> 06:54.247
OH, GOD. COME ON.

06:54.281 --> 06:55.883
THERE'S GONNA BE
NO RECORD EXECUTIVES

06:55.916 --> 06:57.117
AT THE KASTIVIA-
PHAPH WEDDING.

06:57.150 --> 06:59.753
BUT MAYBE THERE'LL
BE SOME BABES, THOUGH, HUH?

06:59.787 --> 07:00.588
YEAH, THERE'LL
BE SOME BABES.

07:00.621 --> 07:01.388
THERE'S GONNA
BE SOME BABES THERE,

07:01.421 --> 07:02.756
AND I'M GONNA GET
ALL OF THEM BABES.

07:02.790 --> 07:03.624
THEY'RE GONNA
GET ALL OF ME,

07:03.657 --> 07:05.593
'CAUSE THAT'S THE WAY
IT IS. GUITARS...

07:05.626 --> 07:08.195
Sean: NO, NO,
AND THE FRONT MAN
DOESN'T GET THE BABES?

07:08.228 --> 07:09.730
COME ON.
ASK MICK JAGGER.

07:09.763 --> 07:11.098
I'M SORRY, DUDES.
IT'S THE DRUMMER.

07:11.131 --> 07:12.666
LOOK, DRUMMERS
ARE GARGOYLES, MAN.

07:12.700 --> 07:13.601
THAT'S WHY YOU
STICK 'EM IN BACK.

07:13.634 --> 07:16.770
THE DRUMMER GETS IN LINE
BEHIND THE ROADIES.

07:16.804 --> 07:18.038
ALL RIGHT, LOOK,
A COUPLE OF WEEKS AGO,

07:18.071 --> 07:18.972
ALL RIGHT, ME AND MY BOYS,

07:19.006 --> 07:20.808
WE PLAYED THIS GIG
OVER AT THE BAYSIDE LANES.

07:20.841 --> 07:22.943
NO LIE. THIS CHICK,
SHE COMES WALKIN' UP

07:22.976 --> 07:24.812
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF MY SET.

07:24.845 --> 07:28.982
SHE PUTS HER BOOBS
ON MY HIGH HAT.

07:29.817 --> 07:31.952
THAT I HAVE
NEVER SEEN.

07:31.985 --> 07:33.854
I HAVE.

07:33.887 --> 07:34.988
WELL, IT'S NICE
YOU'RE ABLE

07:35.022 --> 07:37.825
TO BE AN INFLUENCE
IN A YOUNG MAN'S LIFE.

07:37.858 --> 07:39.560
OH, MAN, WE WERE
HAVING A GREAT TIME

07:39.593 --> 07:41.762
BEING IN A BAND AGAIN.
IT'S JUST...

07:41.795 --> 07:45.065
PROBLEM WAS, WE STARTED
DEVELOPING A FOLLOWING.

07:52.205 --> 07:54.041
Sean: HEY, LILY.

07:54.074 --> 07:54.875
HEY.

07:54.908 --> 07:56.944
THIS IS DEAN. DEAN,
MY DAUGHTER LILY.

07:56.977 --> 07:58.846
HEY.
HEY.

07:58.879 --> 08:00.748
WHERE DO YOU GO?

08:00.781 --> 08:01.882
LaGUARDIA.

08:01.915 --> 08:07.087
PUBLIC.
I'M AT ST. FINNIAN'S.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.922
BUMMER.

08:08.956 --> 08:11.859
YEAH.

08:11.892 --> 08:15.062
OOF!

08:15.095 --> 08:16.029
COULD YOU PICK
THAT UP, PLEASE?

08:16.063 --> 08:21.001
UH, OK, WHAT?
SO NOW, I'M, LIKE,
YOUR ROADIE?

08:21.034 --> 08:22.536
NO, IT'S JUST
YOU KNOCKED IT DOWN.

08:22.570 --> 08:23.971
IT'D BE COOL
IF YOU PICKED IT UP.

08:24.004 --> 08:25.238
THAT'S FINE.
THAT'S FINE, OK.

08:25.272 --> 08:26.239
I HAVE NOTHING
BETTER TO DO

08:26.273 --> 08:28.308
THAN HANG AROUND HERE
AND BE YOUR STUPID ROADIE.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.544
LILY, WE DON'T NEED
A ROADIE.

08:30.578 --> 08:31.679
DAD, DON'T
BE A MARTYR, OK?

08:31.712 --> 08:35.148
I'LL BE YOUR STUPID ROADIE.
HAPPY NOW?

08:38.819 --> 08:39.953
DEAN, COUNT US IN,
ALL RIGHT?

08:39.987 --> 08:41.254
RIGHT.

09:18.258 --> 09:20.227
WHOO!

09:26.734 --> 09:28.068
PUT YOUR HAND HERE, DADDY.

09:28.101 --> 09:30.638
YOU CAN FEEL HIM DRUMMING.

09:33.106 --> 09:35.943
OVER MY DEAD BODY!

09:39.046 --> 09:42.015
* OVER MY DEAD BODY

09:42.049 --> 09:43.984
* OVER MY DEAD BODY

09:44.017 --> 09:47.788
* OVER MY DEAD BODY

09:47.821 --> 09:50.891
* OVER MY DEAD BODY

09:52.726 --> 09:53.360
HOW CAN I BE A ROBOT

09:53.393 --> 09:54.828
AND HAVE ALL
THESE MEMORIES?

09:54.862 --> 09:56.964
BUT YOU REMEMBER
BEING A BABY?

09:56.997 --> 09:59.166
NOBODY REMEMBERS
BEING A BABY.

09:59.199 --> 10:01.969
I DO. EVERYBODY DOES.

10:02.002 --> 10:05.038
I MEAN, I REMEMBER
SLEEPING IN MY CRIB.

10:05.072 --> 10:07.107
I REMEMBER
PEEING IN MY DIAPER.

10:07.140 --> 10:10.143
YOU KNOW,
I EVEN REMEMBER

10:10.177 --> 10:11.745
THE DAY THEY
SWITCHED YOU ON.

10:11.779 --> 10:15.916
NO WAY. I'M GONNA
ASK MOM ABOUT THAT.

10:15.949 --> 10:17.751
GO AHEAD. SHE'S NOT
GONNA TELL YOU THE TRUTH.

10:17.785 --> 10:20.320
SHE'S JUST GONNA SAY
"HENRY, STOP BEING SILLY."

10:20.353 --> 10:23.791
LINA, I KNOW.
I'M WORKING ON HIM.
I PROMISE.

10:23.824 --> 10:24.658
MOM.

10:24.692 --> 10:25.926
YEAH, YEAH,
HOLD ON.

10:25.959 --> 10:26.827
Yeah.

10:26.860 --> 10:28.729
AM I A ROBOT?

10:30.764 --> 10:32.866
HENRY, STOP BEING SILLY.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.036
OH, MY GOD.

10:36.069 --> 10:38.772
I A ROBOT.

10:38.806 --> 10:40.741
I DON'T GET IT.

10:40.774 --> 10:42.876
IF THAT ORGAN GRINDER
WAS AFTER LILY,

10:42.910 --> 10:44.912
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST
GET RID OF HIM?

10:44.945 --> 10:46.947
DAD, DAD,
IT'S NOT SO SIMPLE.

10:46.980 --> 10:47.715
YOU NEVER HAD DAUGHTERS.

10:47.748 --> 10:49.449
SEE, IF SHE WOULD
HAVE FIGURED OUT

10:49.482 --> 10:51.284
THAT I WAS TRYING
TO PUSH THEM APART,

10:51.318 --> 10:54.287
IT WOULD ONLY
DRIVE THEM TOGETHER.

10:55.255 --> 10:56.890
UH-HUH. YES.

10:56.924 --> 10:58.391
YES, HE'S HERE.
HOLD ON.

10:58.425 --> 10:59.893
SEAN, IT'S LINA.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

10:59.927 --> 11:00.894
I THINK YOU SHOULD
EXPLAIN TO HER

11:00.928 --> 11:01.895
WHAT THE HELL
YOU'RE DOING.

11:01.929 --> 11:03.831
I HAVE NOTHING
TO SAY TO HER.

11:03.864 --> 11:04.798
TAKE IT.
NO, NO, NO!

11:04.832 --> 11:07.234
TAKE IT!
NO! IT IS BAD LUCK

11:07.267 --> 11:09.102
TO TALK TO A BRIDE
ON HER WEDDING DAY.

11:09.136 --> 11:11.138
OH, IT IS ONLY BAD LUCK
IF YOU SEE HER,

11:11.171 --> 11:11.839
AND IF YOU'RE THE GROOM.

11:11.872 --> 11:13.206
OK, ENOUGH
HAS HAPPENED TODAY.

11:13.240 --> 11:14.274
I JUST DON'T
WANNA RISK IT.

11:14.307 --> 11:17.344
RISK WHAT? THIS ISN'T ABOUT
FATE, THIS IS ABOUT YOU.

11:17.377 --> 11:19.479
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO, THIS IS
ABOUT YOU, OK?

11:19.512 --> 11:23.150
THIS IS ABOUT YOU
AND YOUR GENES.

11:24.985 --> 11:26.119
MY GENES?
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

11:26.153 --> 11:28.789
YOU HAVE A THING
FOR MUSICIANS, OK?

11:28.822 --> 11:29.689
IT'S IN YOUR DNA,

11:29.723 --> 11:31.992
AND NOW
YOU'VE PASSED
THIS GROUPIE GENE

11:32.025 --> 11:33.160
ONTO OUR DAUGHTER.

11:33.193 --> 11:36.964
OH, THAT
IS SO INSULTING.

11:36.997 --> 11:38.331
HOW SHALLOW
DO YOU THINK I AM?

11:38.365 --> 11:39.933
LOOK, WHY DID YOU
FALL FOR ME, OK?

11:39.967 --> 11:42.302
BECAUSE
I WAS IN A BAND.

11:42.335 --> 11:44.872
AND LOTS
OF OTHER REASONS.

11:44.905 --> 11:48.809
OH, YEAH?
GIMME ONE.

11:48.842 --> 11:49.877
YOU HAVE
BEAUTIFUL HANDS.

11:49.910 --> 11:53.814
I HAVE NAGGLY WHITE,
FRECKLY PASTY

11:53.847 --> 11:55.448
PINK IRISH HANDS.
YOU'RE LYING.

11:55.482 --> 11:57.751
OOH! UGH!

11:57.785 --> 11:59.853
YES, I'M
STILL HERE!

11:59.887 --> 12:00.720
HEY, DAD.

12:00.754 --> 12:03.523
HEY, EDDIE,
DID YOU BRING ME
ANY CAKE?

12:03.556 --> 12:04.257
NO.

12:04.291 --> 12:06.794
BUT I BROUGHT YOU
SOME SHRIMPS.

12:06.827 --> 12:09.997
JUMBO!

12:10.030 --> 12:11.965
WHAT'S THIS GUY
DOING IN MY HOUSE?

12:11.999 --> 12:13.934
OH, SAME AS ME.
HE WANTS HIS MONEY.

12:13.967 --> 12:17.905
OH, OH, I THOUGHT
HE WAS ALL ABOUT THE MUSIC.

12:17.938 --> 12:19.973
YEAH, BIG PROBLEM.
THERE WASN'T ANY MUSIC,

12:20.007 --> 12:21.108
SO I WANT MY MONEY.

12:21.141 --> 12:23.143
I WASN'T ASKING YOU.

12:23.176 --> 12:24.812
HEY, WAIT
IN THE KITCHEN.

12:24.845 --> 12:26.213
I'LL HANDLE THIS.

12:26.246 --> 12:27.547
SO
YOU'RE DEAN?

12:27.580 --> 12:28.248
YEAH, WHY?

12:28.281 --> 12:29.883
HEY, WATCH
THE SASS, MUSIC BOY,

12:29.917 --> 12:32.019
I GOT DISPOSABLE
RAZORS OLDER THAN YOU.

12:32.052 --> 12:33.520
HEY, WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

12:33.553 --> 12:38.859
2 THINGS...I'M OLDER
AND I'VE GOT RAZORS.

12:38.892 --> 12:39.759
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

12:39.793 --> 12:43.130
YOU'VE BEEN
ACTING LIKE A JERK
ALL WEEK.

12:48.201 --> 12:49.169
TOWEL?

12:49.202 --> 12:50.037
NO, THANKS.

12:50.070 --> 12:52.339
UH, YOU'RE LOOKING
A LITTLE SWEATY THERE.

12:52.372 --> 12:54.207
NO, IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'M COOL.

12:54.241 --> 12:56.910
I-I'LL JUST
LEAVE THIS HERE.

12:56.944 --> 12:58.578
HE DOESN'T
WANT A TOWEL, OK!

12:58.611 --> 13:01.014
HE TOLD YOU HE
DOESN'T WANT A TOWEL,

13:01.048 --> 13:01.815
SO WHY ARE YOU
TRYING TO FORCE

13:01.849 --> 13:03.984
A TOWEL ON A MAN
WHO QUITE OBVIOUSLY

13:04.017 --> 13:06.286
IS NOT IN NEED
OF A TOWEL?

13:06.319 --> 13:09.857
OK?!

13:10.123 --> 13:12.926
I CAN DO IT.
I'M CLASSICALLY TRAINED.

13:12.960 --> 13:13.894
STOP FOLLOWING ME!

13:13.927 --> 13:15.996
JUST ASK YOUR DAD
TO GIVE ME
ANOTHER CHANCE.

13:16.029 --> 13:18.966
