PLAY IT.

15:19.119 --> 15:20.620
OH! OH, GOD.

15:20.653 --> 15:24.091
SHE DOESN'T HAVE
A PLAY LIST.

15:25.092 --> 15:26.059
OH, DEAR GOD!

15:26.093 --> 15:28.128
COME ON, IT'S JUST
A FEW SONGS.

15:28.161 --> 15:29.963
IT'S HER WEDDING.

15:29.997 --> 15:31.264
PEACHES AND ERB?

15:31.298 --> 15:33.633
HERB. THEY'RE ARE
WORSE SONGS.

15:33.666 --> 15:38.105
OH, YEAH, HOW ABOUT
SOMETIMES WHEN WE TOUCH?

15:38.138 --> 15:40.373
DID YOU
PEEK AT THIS?

15:40.407 --> 15:44.277
OH, NO! JUST KILL ME,
GOD, NOW, PLEASE.

15:44.311 --> 15:46.113
THERE'S SOME
ROCKERS ON THERE.

15:46.146 --> 15:49.549
WHAT, LOOK, Y.M.C.A?

15:49.582 --> 15:51.384
WELL, YOU WOULDN'T
HAVE TO DO THAT ONE
ALONE, HUH?

15:51.418 --> 15:54.254
EVERYONE'LL BE
SINGING ALONG, DOING
THE LITTLE DANCE--

15:54.287 --> 15:56.189
BABY, DO WE HAVE TO
DO THIS?

15:56.223 --> 15:57.257
YES.

15:57.290 --> 15:58.758
OHH, NO!

15:58.791 --> 16:01.194
COME ON, BABY.

16:01.228 --> 16:03.430
I LOVE YOU.

16:03.463 --> 16:06.466
* I HONESTLY LOVE YOU

16:10.103 --> 16:12.039
OH, NO.

16:12.072 --> 16:13.506
REUNITED?

16:13.540 --> 16:18.078
* AND IT FEELS SO GOOD

16:18.111 --> 16:23.250
* REUNITED 'CAUSE WE
UNDERSTOOD *

16:23.283 --> 16:25.618
* THERE'S ONE
PERFECT THING *

16:25.652 --> 16:29.789
* AND, SUGAR,
THIS ONE IS IT *

16:29.822 --> 16:34.161
* WE BOTH ARE SO EXCITED
'CAUSE WE'RE *

16:34.194 --> 16:39.199
* REUNITED, HEY, HEY

16:39.232 --> 16:40.067
SO THERE ARE I AM

16:40.100 --> 16:42.602
PLAYING SOFT ROCK HITS
FROM THE SEVENTIES

16:42.635 --> 16:44.104
AND BEYOND, ALL RIGHT,

16:44.137 --> 16:45.672
AND I'M WATCHING
MY DAUGHTER

16:45.705 --> 16:49.142
MOPPING SWEAT OFF
THE GUY WHO'S...

16:49.176 --> 16:52.045
GONNA MAKE YOU
THE YOUNGEST
GRANDFATHER

16:52.079 --> 16:55.182
SINCE, UH...ME?

16:55.215 --> 16:56.249
YEAH.

16:56.283 --> 16:58.218
YEAH, DAD, YEAH,
YEAH, HONESTLY,

16:58.251 --> 16:59.452
THAT'S WHAT I WAS
AFRAID OF, YOU KNOW,

16:59.486 --> 17:01.188
AND I THOUGHT I HAD
NO WAY OUT,

17:01.221 --> 17:04.624
AND THEN, OK,
LIKE A GIFT FROM THE GODS,

17:04.657 --> 17:06.093
THIS KID DEAN HANDS ME

17:06.126 --> 17:09.362
THE WEAPON OF HIS OWN
DESTRUCTION.

17:09.396 --> 17:10.163
I CAN'T BELIEVE

17:10.197 --> 17:12.199
I ACTUALLY HAVE TO
PLAY THESE SONGS.

17:12.232 --> 17:14.334
I KNOW. IT IS
SO UNCOOL.

17:14.367 --> 17:16.203
NO OFFENSE
OR ANYTHING, LILY,

17:16.236 --> 17:19.472
BUT YOUR OLD MAN'S
A BUTTWAD.

17:20.240 --> 17:21.040
NONE TAKEN.

17:21.074 --> 17:22.742
I THOUGHT--I THOUGHT
HE WANTED TO ROCK.

17:22.775 --> 17:24.311
HE DOESN'T
WANT TO ROCK,

17:24.344 --> 17:24.977
I WANT TO ROCK.

17:25.011 --> 17:27.347
I KNOW, I KNOW,
IT'S SO SAD.

17:27.380 --> 17:29.782
AND THE OTHER DAY
I CAUGHT HIM WATCHING VH1.

17:29.816 --> 17:31.684
I CAN'T STAND
THIS STUFF.

17:31.718 --> 17:33.153
HOW AM I
SUPPOSED TO PLAY

17:33.186 --> 17:36.323
THE CHICKEN DANCE
AND NOT THROW UP?

17:36.356 --> 17:38.291
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?
MAYBE--

17:38.325 --> 17:40.193
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
THROW UP, YOU KNOW?

17:40.227 --> 17:42.262
THAT'LL SHOW HIM.

17:42.295 --> 17:43.096
MAYBE I SHOULD.

17:43.130 --> 17:45.732
MAYBE SHOULD BECAUSE
I HAVE INTEGRITY.

17:45.765 --> 17:47.300
HELL, YEAH.
YEAH.

17:47.334 --> 17:49.136
THERE IT WAS,
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME,

17:49.169 --> 17:50.203
DEAN'S ACHILLES HEEL.

17:50.237 --> 17:54.641
INTEGRITY, MAN!
I HAVE INTEGRITY!

17:55.342 --> 17:58.745
WHAT THE HOLY HECK
DO TEENAGERS KNOW
ABOUT INTEGRITY?

17:58.778 --> 18:02.715
NOTHING, BUT THEY TAKE IT
VERY SERIOUSLY.

18:02.749 --> 18:07.854
* REUNITED, HEY, HEY

18:07.887 --> 18:10.390
OH, YEAH, YEAH,
THAT WAS GOOD, GOOD.

18:10.423 --> 18:11.424
OH, JUST
A COUPLE THINGS.

18:11.458 --> 18:14.194
UM, DEAN,
YOU KNOW THAT PART
WHERE I'M SINGING...

18:14.227 --> 18:19.766
* LOVER, LOVER,
THIS IS SOLID LOVE *

18:19.799 --> 18:22.402
* AND YOU'RE EXACTLY
WHAT I-- *

18:22.435 --> 18:23.836
YOU KNOW THAT PART
I'M TALKING ABOUT?

18:23.870 --> 18:26.473
AT THE PAUSE,
CAN YOU JUST SPIN
YOUR STICK

18:26.506 --> 18:28.208
LIKE THE DRUMMER
FROM LOVERBOY?

18:28.241 --> 18:30.243
THAT WOULD BE
JUST AWESOME.

18:31.244 --> 18:32.111
EXCUSE ME?
NOTHING.

18:32.145 --> 18:33.213
NO, I THOUGHT
I HEARD YOU SAY
SOMETHING.

18:33.246 --> 18:36.249
PLEASE, PLEASE,
DON'T--IF YOU HAVE
SOMETHING TO SAY,

18:36.283 --> 18:37.350
SAY IT. I DON'T
WANT TO STIFLE

18:37.384 --> 18:42.155
ANYONE'S CREATIVITY
OR INTEGRITY.

18:42.889 --> 18:44.324
LOOK, IT'S JUST, UH...

18:44.357 --> 18:46.393
THIS SONG'S CRAP.

18:46.426 --> 18:47.560
EXCUSE ME?

18:47.594 --> 18:48.561
IT'S A CRAPPY SONG.

18:48.595 --> 18:51.364
I DON'T SEE WHAT YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND ABOUT THAT.

18:51.398 --> 18:53.266
WOW.

18:53.300 --> 18:54.066
CRAPPY SONG, HUH?

18:54.100 --> 18:55.702
I HAPPEN TO THINK
THIS IS A CLASSIC.

18:55.735 --> 18:59.339
REUNITED
IS A HAUNTING
EXPRESSION

18:59.372 --> 19:02.209
OF PURE, HOT HUMAN
NEED AND DESIRE,

19:02.242 --> 19:04.377
AND IF YOU
CAN'T UNDERSTAND

19:04.411 --> 19:06.446
THE AESTHETIC BEAUTY
OF PEACHES AND ERB--

19:06.479 --> 19:07.113
HERB.

19:07.146 --> 19:10.383
THEN YOU CAN--
I WOULD GLADLY

19:10.417 --> 19:12.352
AND WILLINGLY ACCEPT
YOUR RESIGNATION

19:12.385 --> 19:15.422
FROM THIS CRAPPY
BAND RIGHT NOW.

19:15.455 --> 19:17.624
SO IF YOU'LL
EXCUSE US, OK,

19:17.657 --> 19:19.792
SOME OF US HAVE
A WEDDING TO PLAY.

19:19.826 --> 19:22.662
SORRY IT DIDN'T
WORK OUT.

19:22.695 --> 19:25.232
CAN WE TAKE IT FROM
THE TOP, PLEASE?

19:25.265 --> 19:26.366
NO.

19:26.399 --> 19:27.634
EXCUSE ME?

19:27.667 --> 19:29.902
NO, HE'S RIGHT.
THESE SONGS BLOW.

19:29.936 --> 19:31.804
OH, WAIT, SO YOU'RE
QUITTING, TOO?

19:31.838 --> 19:32.939
I'M NOT QUITTING.

19:32.972 --> 19:34.941
I'M SAYING YOU SHOULD
BE FIRED.

19:34.974 --> 19:38.278
YOU CAN'T FIRE ME.
THIS IS MY BAND.

19:38.311 --> 19:40.780
IT'S NOT MUCH OF A BAND
WITHOUT US.

19:40.980 --> 19:42.415
ALL RIGHT, FINE,
THEN, FINE.

19:42.449 --> 19:44.517
ALL RIGHT, FINE,
I QUIT, OK?

19:44.551 --> 19:47.520
BUT I'M TAKING
MY STUFF WITH ME.
GIVE ME MY GUITAR.

19:47.554 --> 19:50.290
COME AND GET IT,
.

19:52.425 --> 19:53.960
WOO-HOO, OK!

19:53.993 --> 19:57.397
SO YOU MADE
YOUR BRAVE STAND
FOR PEACHES AND HERB

19:57.430 --> 19:58.465
AND IT WAS
A WONDERFUL EFFORT

19:58.498 --> 20:01.568
AND YOU LOOK
LIKE AN IDIOT.

20:01.601 --> 20:02.902
NICELY DONE.

20:02.935 --> 20:04.337
THANK YOU.

20:04.371 --> 20:05.972
YEAH, BUT LOOK, BABE,

20:06.005 --> 20:08.875
IF, UH, IF LILY'S GOT
THIS GROUPIE GENE,

20:08.908 --> 20:10.610
YOU'RE SCREWED.

20:10.843 --> 20:13.946
MY FATHER COULDN'T STOP IT
AND NEITHER CAN YOU.

20:13.980 --> 20:15.348
HEY, I'VE GOT
PLENTY OF I--

20:15.382 --> 20:18.385
UH-UH-UH, IT'S WAY
OUT OF YOUR PASTY,

20:18.418 --> 20:21.554
FRECKLED,
IRISH HANDS.

20:24.657 --> 20:30.463
* REUNITED AND IT
FEELS SO GOOD *

20:30.497 --> 20:36.469
* REUNITED 'CAUSE
WE UNDERSTOOD *

20:36.503 --> 20:38.871
* THERE'S ONE
PERFECT FIT *

20:38.905 --> 20:42.909
* AND, SUGAR,
THIS ONE IS IT *

20:42.942 --> 20:47.347
* WE BOTH ARE SO EXCITED
'CAUSE WE'RE *

